-- Peru Stock Movers: Atacocha, Candente Copper, Panoro
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-06-22T21:34:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-22/peru-stock-movers-atacocha-candente-copper-panoro.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of market close in Lima.  The  Lima General Index (IGBVL)  rose 0.4 percent to 20,509.26. The
MSCI All Peru Capped Index slid 0.3 percent to 2,727.27.  Candente Copper Corp. (DNT)  , a Canadian mining
exploration company with operations in Peru, rose 1.8 percent to
56 cents after the company said villagers will vote July 8 on a
three-year surface access agreement for its Canariaco copper
project.  Panoro Minerals Ltd. (PML)  , a Canadian copper and gold
exploration company, fell for a third session, losing 3.1
percent to 63 cents after copper dropped to a six-month low in
 London .  Cia. Minera Atacocha SA (ATACOBC1 PE), a Lima-based zinc
mining company, slid 2.2 percent to 44 centimos after zinc
futures declined for a third session in London.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Emery in  Lima  at 
 aemery1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
